# Testing Enforcement

**CRITICAL**: Frontend changes MUST be tested with Playwright before pushing.

## Before EVERY Push

```bash
npm run build              # TypeScript/compile check
npm run test:ui            # Run affected tests
# Fix failures before pushing
```

## Requirements by Change Type

| Change | Required Tests |
|--------|----------------|
| New feature | New test file |
| Bug fix | Regression test |
| UI change | Interaction tests |
| Navigation | URL/routing tests |

## Common Patterns

### Testing Navigation/URL
```typescript
test('uses correct URL params', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.click('[data-testid="item"]');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\?c=/);  // correct param
});
```

### Testing Forms
```typescript
test('submits form', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.fill('[data-testid="email"]', 'test@example.com');
  await page.click('[data-testid="submit"]');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/success');
});
```

## What NOT To Do

- ❌ Push without tests
- ❌ Use `waitForTimeout()` (use smart waits)
- ❌ Test implementation details
- ❌ Rely on text that changes

_Playwright offers same functionality as Cypress with better speed and multi-browser support._
